From Gordon Banks Subject Re request for information on essential tremor and Indrol In article q tbnINN writes Essential tremor is a progressive hereditary tremor that gets worse when the patient tries to use the effected member All limbs, vocal cords, and head can be involved Inderal is a beta blocker and is usually effective in diminishing the tremor Alcohol and mysoline are also effective, but alcohol is too toxic to use as a treatment Gordon Banks N JXP Skepticism is the chastity of the intellect, and it is shameful to surrender it too soon